## Configure Parameters

### Parameter Context Values

| Parameter | Value |
|-----------|-------|
| `Jira URL` | `{{ jira_url }}` |
| `Jira Email` | `{{ jira_email }}` |
| `Project Names - Simple Query` | `{{ jira_project_keys }}` |
| `Snowflake Role` | `{{ runtime_role | upper }}` |
| `Snowflake Database` | `{{ dest_db | upper }}` |
| `Snowflake Schema` | `{{ dest_schema | upper }}` |
| `Snowflake Warehouse` | `{{ warehouse_name | upper }}` |
| `Snowflake Table` | `{{ dest_table | upper }}` |
| `Authentication Strategy` | `SNOWFLAKE_MANAGED` |
| `Jira API Token` | *(provided at runtime тАФ not stored in answers)* |

### Get the Parameter Context ID

```bash
nipyapi --profile {{ nipyapi_profile }} canvas list_all_process_groups
```

Find the Jira process group and note its parameter context ID.

### Run the Configure Script

```bash
python scripts/configure_jira_params.py \
  --profile {{ nipyapi_profile }} \
  --ctx-id <parameter_context_id> \
  --jira-url "{{ jira_url }}" \
  --jira-email "{{ jira_email }}" \
  --jira-token "<your_api_token>" \
  --snowflake-role "{{ runtime_role | upper }}" \
  --snowflake-database "{{ dest_db | upper }}" \
  --snowflake-schema "{{ dest_schema | upper }}" \
  --snowflake-warehouse "{{ warehouse_name | upper }}" \
  --snowflake-table "{{ dest_table | upper }}" \
  --project-keys "{{ jira_project_keys }}"
```

Expected response: `200`

> The `configure_jira_params.py` script uses direct HTTP calls instead of nipyapi because nipyapi has known issues updating sensitive parameters.
